title: Takagi Masakatsu - COIEDA
description:
[IMG]http://i139.photobucket.com/albums/q292/plastic_255/R-333636-1127312163.jpg[/IMG]

Coeida is a great addition to Masakatsu&#039;s collection of works. It perfectly encapsulates all of the positivity associated with the spring and summer seasons. In this regard, it&#039;s more reminiscent of the the more rhythmic Eating and Eating 2 releases than it is of his more experimental and atonal Pia and Opus Pia albums. The album has songs that are sometimes mostly piano-based and even one featuring David Sylvian (on "Exit/Delete"). Even though Masakatsu&#039;s aural works are mostly concentrated within the realm of electronic music, it&#039;s an album that&#039;s more contingent on the listener&#039;s mood than their genre preference.
